===Etymology===
Modern Latin, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|ἥλιος||lang=grc|sun}} (because its presence was first theorised in the sun's atmosphere).

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|hē'lēəm}}, {{IPA|/ˈhiːlɪəm/}}, {{SAMPA|/"hi:li@m/}}
* {{hyphenation|he|li|um}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{uncountable}} A [[colorless]] and [[inert]] gas, and the second lightest chemical [[element]] (''symbol'' He) with an [[atomic number]] of 2 and [[atomic weight]] of 4.002602.
# {{countable}} A form or sample of the element.

